  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The investigators hypothesize that baseline plasma brain natriuretic peptide (BNP) and
      migration inhibitory factor (MIF) levels are surrogate markers of clinical severity of PAH
      and that changes in plasma brain natriuretic peptide (BNP) and MIF levels pre and post
      exercise.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
