  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Confirmed diagnosis of PAH, based on currently accepted gold standard for Right Heart
             Catheterization.

          -  Patients with mean artery pressure of greater that 25 mm Hg at rest or 30mm Hg during
             exercise with pulmonary capillary wedge pressure less than 18mm Hg on right heart
             catheterization.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Significant left heart disease or renal insufficiency (serum creatinine &gt; 1.5 mg%).
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
